# Milestone planning discipline (mandatory)

Before writing ANY code for a new milestone (M3 and beyond), produce a
planning review as a Canvas document containing:

- Architecture review
- Affected files list
- Migration impact analysis
- Route impact analysis
- Testing plan
- Implementation order
- Acceptance criteria

No coding starts until that review is explicitly approved by the user.

Architecture boundaries that reviews must preserve (unless explicitly
re-decided): Auth.js session boundary, `OrgContext` + `orgScoped` tenant
isolation, service layer owning all DB access and audit writes, PostgreSQL +
Drizzle, single Next.js app. No queues, RLS, microservices, or managed auth
providers without an approved ADR.
